## Overview
Develop a robust Admin Dashboard for platform administrators to manage accounts, monitor usage and system health, handle moderation tasks, enforce security/compliance controls, and support internal workflows. This admin hub will connect tightly with Admin Tools & Moderation, User Authentication, Session Management, and Security/Privacy/Compliance features, and include a dedicated Admin - User Management page for live intervention, impersonation, and escalations.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
The Admin Dashboard is the central platform admin area designed to give operators visibility into the entire system and direct action capability. Goals:
- Provide a high-level overview of accounts, usage metrics, system health, and ongoing requests.
- Offer Admin Tools & Moderation capabilities to manage users, workspaces, billing exceptions, disputes, and support escalations.
- Ensure secure authentication flows, workspace life cycle management, and token/session lifecycle governance.
- Enforce data governance, retention, audit logging, and enterprise privacy controls with export capabilities.
- Supply a focused UI for Admin - User Management to view and intervene in customer workspaces, impersonate accounts for support, and perform escalations.

Connected features:
- Admin Tools & Moderation: Tools to block/disable accounts, modify workspaces, apply billing exceptions, resolve disputes, escalate support tickets.
- User Authentication: Sign-up/login flows, OAuth integrations, and creation/managing of workspaces tied to accounts.
- Session Management: Issue/refresh/revoke tokens, enforce single-use refresh tokens, monitor active sessions.
- Security, Privacy & Compliance: Data export, retention policies, audit logs, enterprise privacy controls.
- Admin - User Management: View and intervene in customer workspaces, impersonation for support, escalation actions.

UI guidance and expectations:
- High-level dashboards with Accounts Overview, System Health, Support Queue, Usage & Billing, and Feature Toggles.
- Card-based layout with clear hierarchies; tables with sortable columns; charts showing key metrics (uptime, errors, queue length, usage).
- Quick actions: impersonate, escalate, export data, apply policy changes, enable/disable features.
- Visual consistency with the project’s design system: soft shadows, rounded corners, gentle color palette, accessible typography, and responsive behavior.

Note: No external API integrations are mandated by the project context, but the design should be ready to connect to your existing services (auth, user/workspace management, billing, logs, and audit systems) via well-defined REST/GraphQL endpoints.

## Components to Build
- Admin Dashboard Shell
  - Top navigation with pill-shaped tabs; Active state uses deep green (#195C4A).
  - Left-hand secondary navigation (collapsible sections).
  - User profile actions on the right (search, add, profile menu).
- Accounts Overview Card
  - Metrics: total active workspaces, trial signups, plan distribution, churn rate.
  - Visual: compact KPI tiles, small trend charts.
- System Health Panel
  - Uptime, API latency, queue backlogs, recent errors, health statuses.
  - Real-time/near-time data visualization.
- Usage & Requests Panel
  - Traffic, API usage, rate limits, pending requests, support escalations.
- Support Queue Panel
  - Flagged disputes, billing tickets, escalation statuses; action buttons for review, escalate, approve/deny.
- Admin Tools & Moderation Panel
  - User management (suspend/activate, role changes), Workspace management (merge/split, suspend, rename), Billing exceptions (manual adjustments), Disputes resolution, Support escalations routing.
- Admin - User Management Page
  - Workspace list with actions: impersonate, escalate, export, view details.
  - Impersonation workflow modal with safeguards (confirmation, audit log, sandbox mode).
  - Escalation actions and notes, with audit trail.
- Data Export & Compliance Panel
  - Export job queue, policy editor (retention), audit log viewer/search, privacy controls toggles.
- Feature Toggles & Settings
  - Enable/disable enterprise features, rollout controls, environment flags.

Technical details for components:
- Reusable Card components with header/body/actions regions.
- Data Table components with sorting, filtering, pagination, row-level actions.
- KPI/Stat components with color-coded deltas and status badges.
- Chart components for system metrics (line/area charts with minimal grid).

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Pages/Routes
  - /admin/dashboard (Admin Dashboard)
  - /admin/users (Admin - User Management)
  - /admin/tools (Admin Tools & Moderation)
  - /admin/settings (Feature Toggles & Compliance)
- UI Components
  - Card, KPI Tile, DataTable, ChartCard
  - Modal dialogs for impersonation, confirmation, and export
  - Tabs/Nav with accessible keyboard navigation
  - Action Buttons: primary, secondary, danger states
  - Status Badges: green, yellow, red states
  - Form controls: search input, select filters, date pickers
- Interactions
  - Hover elevations on cards; click-to-expand sections
  - Inline filtering and sorting in tables
  - Impersonation flow with safety prompts and audit logging
  - Real-time-ish updates for health/status panels (polling or subscriptions as available)
- Accessibility
  - ARIA roles, descriptive labels, keyboard navigable controls
  - Contrast compliance for text on backgrounds
- Performance
  - Lazy loading for heavy tables; pagination for large datasets
  - Debounced search inputs; minimize re-renders

### Backend
- Data Models (db schema)
  - Accounts: id, name, status, plan, created_at, last_active, seats
  - Workspaces: id, account_id, name, status, plan, created_at, last_activity
  - Users: id, account_id, email, role, status, last_login
  - Sessions: id, user_id, token_hash, expires_at, revoked, platform
  - Transactions/Billing: id, account_id, amount, currency, status, reason, created_at
  - AdminAuditLogs: id, admin_id, action, target_type, target_id, timestamp, before_state, after_state
  - Disputes: id, workspace_id, status, escalated_to, notes, created_at, updated_at
  - Exports: id, type, scope, status, created_at, completed_at, location
  - RetentionPolicies: id, scope, duration_days, enabled
  - SystemHealth: captured_at, uptime_pct, api_latency_ms, errors_last_24h, backlog_size
  - FeatureToggles: id, feature_name, enabled, rollout_percentage, environment
- APIs (REST/GraphQL)
  - Admin Dashboard Overview
    - GET /admin/dashboard/summary
  - Accounts/Workspaces
    - GET /admin/accounts
    - GET /admin/accounts/{account_id}/workspaces
    - POST /admin/workspaces/{id}/impersonate
    - POST /admin/workspaces/{id}/escalate
  - User Management
    - GET /admin/users
    - POST /admin/users/{id}/suspend
    - POST /admin/users/{id}/activate
    - POST /admin/users/{id}/impersonate
  - Sessions & Tokens
    - GET /admin/sessions
    - POST /admin/sessions/{id}/revoke
  - Billing & Exceptions
    - GET /admin/billing/exceptions
    - POST /admin/billing/exceptions/{id}/approve
    - POST /admin/billing/exceptions/{id}/reject
  - Disputes & Support Escalations
    - GET /admin/disputes
    - POST /admin/disputes/{id}/resolve
    - POST /admin/disputes/{id}/escalate
  - Exports & Compliance
    - POST /admin/exports
    - GET /admin/audit-logs
    - GET /admin/retention-policies
    - POST /admin/privacy/export
  - Feature Toggles
    - GET /admin/features
    - PATCH /admin/features/{name}
  - Audit & Logs
    - GET /admin/audit-logs
- Database Access
  - Use proper indexing on account_id, workspace_id, user_id, status for fast queries
  - Ensure audit logs capture before_state and after_state for admin actions
- Security
  - Role-based access control: SUPER_ADMIN, ADMIN, SUPPORT
  - Enforce least privilege for admin endpoints; require re-auth for sensitive actions
  - Token/session storage with encryption; support single-use refresh tokens where applicable
- Validation
  - Strict input validation on all endpoints; whitelist acceptable statuses, roles, and actions
  - Ensure impersonation actions generate an audit trail and require confirmation

### Integration
- Data Flow
  - Admin Dashboard fetches summary data from /admin/dashboard/summary
  - Admin pages call respective endpoints for users, workspaces, disputes, exports
  - Impersonation actions route through a controlled session switch with audit logging
- Data Consistency
  - Maintain referential integrity between accounts, workspaces, and users
  - Propagate status changes across related entities (e.g., suspending a user updates workspace access)
- Event Handling
  - Admin actions emit events to audit/logging systems; optionally publish to a message bus for downstream analytics

## User Experience Flow
1) Admin logs in to /admin/dashboard with elevated privileges.
2) Admin reviews Overview: Accounts, System Health, Support Queue, Usage.
3) Admin navigates to Admin - User Management to view customer workspaces.
4) Admin selects a workspace; views details, initiates impersonation for support if needed.
5) If issues require escalation, Admin opens an escalation for the disputed workspace or billing irregularity.
6) Admin uses Admin Tools & Moderation to suspend/activate users, adjust billing exceptions, or resolve disputes.
7) Admin uses Export/Compliance to export data or enforce retention policies.
8) Admin toggles enterprise features via Feature Toggles for rollout planning.
9) All actions are recorded in AdminAuditLogs and visible in Audit Logs panel.

## Technical Specifications
- Data Models: See above under Backend; ensure JSON schema alignment for API payloads.
- API Endpoints: See REST/GraphQL endpoints outline above.
- Security:
  - Authentication: Admin/Privileged access required; OAuth2 or SSO as configured.
  - Authorization: Role-based checks; deny unknown or insufficient privileges.
  - Token Management: Secure issuance, refresh, revocation; single-use refresh tokens if supported.
- Validation:
  - Validate IDs, statuses, and permissions on all endpoints.
  - Validate input payloads for impersonation, escalation, export, and policy updates.

